<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sanctuary" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sanctuary,</orth> a sacred place: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.10.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 10, 19</bibl>. Especially a sacred asylum affording protection from any persecution: <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 4, 31</bibl>.* <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.66" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.4.66" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 4, 66</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.42" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 94</bibl>. <emph>to take s.</emph> == to take refuge in such a place: <bibl n="shak. err 5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 28</bibl>. <emph>to break s.</emph> == to violate it: <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 47</bibl>. <cit><quote>s. men,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 47</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>s. children,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 47</bibl></cit>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>